cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CL 

This paper is likely to belong to the category of cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it presents an architecture for training deep, directed generative models with many layers of latent variables. It also incorporates techniques to improve performance on natural images, which is a common application of machine learning. 

It is also likely to belong to cs.CV (Computer Vision) as the paper specifically mentions experiments on standard image modelling benchmarks and imputations of occluded regions in natural images. 

Additionally, it could belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as generative models are a common area of research in AI. 

cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is another possible category as the paper discusses the use of neural networks in the architecture. 

Finally, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is a less likely category, but still possible as the paper mentions the use of autoregressive models in the reconstruction distribution, which is a technique commonly used in natural language processing.
